Title: REPORT OF COL. T.W. CAHILL, OF THE SECOND CONNECTICUT.
Abstract: CAPTAIN: I have the honor to report that an attack was made early yesterday morning by a Confederate force of about ten regiments, under command of Major-Gen. JOHN C. BRECKINRIDGE, and that after a fight of four hours' duration and of great severity, the enemy were repulsed.
